sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was designed due to inspiration from [Tomoko Ikwaki,Haruyuki lefuji,Yoshikazu Hiraga,Akira Hosomi, Tomotake Morita, Yuko GigaHamam Kaoru Takegawa.???Multiple functions of ergosterol in the fission yeast Schizosaccharomyces pombe???.7 December 2007 ] a direct link is available below http://mic.sgmjournals.org/content/154/3/830.full
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part converts ergosta-5,7,22,24(28)-tetraen-3β-ol to ergosterol. In the presence of UV light ergosterol is converted to Vitamin D2. The coding region[BBa_M36655] produces C-24(28) sterol reductase an enzyme that catalyzes the final step in Vitamin D2 synthesis pathway by converting ergosta-5,7,22,24(28)-tetraen-3β-ol to ergosterol.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This construct uses a strong promoter and 5'UTR so that the amount of C-24(28) sterol reductase is substancial to efficiently convert the precursor to Vitamin D2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Elvis Ikwa, Alexis Garduno, Johnathan Bowes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is derived from Schizosaccharomyces pombe 972h- (strain: 972h-). Gene ID :2541740 in the NCBI database.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Enzyme coding sequence for C-24(28) sterol reductase, an enzyme which acts in the last step of Vitamin D2 synthesis by reducing ergosta-5,7,22,24(28)-tetraenol to ergosterol. No mutations were made to the enzymes genetic sequence. The genetic sequence is optimized for use in Synechococcus elongatus (PCC 7942).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The coding sequence denoted by Gene ID :2541740 has to be codon optimized for Synechococcus elongatus.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Elvis Ikwa, Alexis Garduno, Johnathan Bowes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36724
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (strong), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Vivek Mutalik et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Vivek says, "This is (the) Makoff design, it gives good expression and is seq independent of the Schoner design."
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
